definition.value: An adenosine 5'-phosphate that is coenzyme A in which the phosphate group at position 3' has been replaced by a hydrogen atom. It is an intermediate metabolite in pantothenate and CoA biosynthesis.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any alpha,beta-unsaturated fatty acid.
A glycosylmannose consisting of a beta-D-galactopyranose residue and a D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A hydroxykynurenine  that is kynurenine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
A  dichlorobenzoyl-CoA having 2,4-dichlorobenzoyl as the S-acyl group.
An acyl-CoA having trans-dodec-2-enoyl as the S-acyl group.
An amino disaccharide consistingof alpha-L-fucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.

A branched amino oligosaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are connected branches consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl and beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages respectively.
